    <h2>Method</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>Prepare a baking tray by scrunching greaseproof paper and using it to line the tray, pushing it into the corners and smoothing it to lie flat.</li>
        <li>Melt the peanut butter on gentle heat in saucepan.</li>
        <li>Add coconut oil & melt, stirring.</li>
        <li>Add syrup & melt, stirring.</li>
        <li>Add oats and stir.</li>
        <li>Pour the mixture into the lined baking tray, flattening down with a spatula.</li>
        <li>Refrigerate until "set", and then cut into pieces.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Notes</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>You can add dessicated coconut, sultanas and/or other dried fruits and seeds if you want.</li>
    </ol>


